  • Method Details

    • ingestData

      public IngestionApi.IngestDataAdapter ingestData(String hrn, String layerId, byte[] byteArray, Optional<String> xHEREChecksum, Optional<String> xHERETraceId, Optional<String> xHEREMessageKey, Optional<String> billingTag)
      Sends streaming data to a specified layer in the HERE platform

      Path: /layers/{layerId}

      Method: POST

      Expected answers:

      code 200 : ResponseOkSingle (OK)

      code 400 : Response400 (Bad Request)

      code 401 : (Unauthorized)

      code 404 : Response404 (No handler found)

      code 413 : Response413 (Payload Too Large)

      code 415 : Response415 (Unsupported Media Type)

      code 500 : Response500 (Internal Server Error)

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      layerId - The ID of the layer where you want the data ingested.
      byteArray - A byte array of data to send to the HERE platform for ingestion. The maximum size is 20 MB. Decode the example from base64 before using.
      xHEREChecksum - A base64 encoded SHA-256 hash you can provide for validation against the calculated value on the request body hash. This verifies the integrity of your request and prevents modification by a third party.It will be created by the service if not provided. A SHA-256 hash consists of 256 bits or 64 chars.
      xHERETraceId - A unique message ID, such as a UUID. This can be included in the request if you want to use an ID that you define. If you do not include an ID, one will be generated during ingestion and included in the response. You can use this ID to track your request and identify the message in the catalog.
      xHEREMessageKey - A unique message ID, such as a UUID. This can be included in the request if you want to use an ID that you define. If you do not include an ID, X-HERE-TraceId will be used instead. You can use this ID to specify the partition for the message in the data catalog.
      billingTag - Optional billing tag provided by customer. It will be used in grouping of billing records.

    • ingestPartitions

      public IngestionApi.IngestPartitionsAdapter ingestPartitions(String hrn, String layerId, com.here.platform.data.client.base.generated.scaladsl.model.ingest.PublishPartitions body, Optional<String> xHERETraceId, Optional<String> billingTag)
      Upload partitions to the given layer. For better performance batch your partitions (e.g. 1000 per request), rather than uploading them individually.

      Path: /layers/{layerId}/partitions

      Method: POST

      Expected answers:

      code 200 : ResponseOk (OK)

      code 400 : Response400 (Bad Request)

      code 401 : (Unauthorized)

      code 404 : Response404 (No handler found)

      code 413 : Response413 (Payload Too Large)

      code 415 : Response415 (Unsupported Media Type)

      code 500 : Response500 (Internal Server Error)

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      layerId - The ID of the layer where you want the data ingested.
      body - Publication partitions. Data and DataHandle fields cannot be populated at the same time. See Partition object for more details on body fields
      xHERETraceId - A unique message ID, such as a UUID. This can be included in the request if you want to use an ID that you define. If you do not include an ID, one will be generated during ingestion and included in the response. You can use this ID to track your request and identify the message in the catalog. X-HERE-TraceId is passed as dsTraceId kafka record header.
      billingTag - Optional billing tag provided by customer. It will be used in grouping of billing records.

    • ingestSDII

      public IngestionApi.IngestSDIIAdapter ingestSDII(String hrn, String layerId, byte[] byteArray, Optional<String> xHEREChecksum, Optional<String> xHERETraceId, Optional<String> xHEREMessageKey, Optional<String> billingTag)
      Consumes individual SDII messages and SDII MessageLists. The endpoint automatically breaks SDII MessageLists down and stores the data as individual SDII messages. Note that this endpoint does not support compression. If you are sending data to stream layer that has compression enabled, you must use the /layers/ endpoint and all compression and decompression must be handled by your application.

      Path: /layers/{layerId}/sdiiMessageList

      Method: POST

      Expected answers:

      code 200 : ResponseOk (OK)

      code 400 : Response400 (Bad Request)

      code 401 : (Unauthorized)

      code 404 : Response404 (No handler found)

      code 413 : Response413 (Payload Too Large)

      code 415 : Response415 (Unsupported Media Type)

      code 500 : Response500 (Internal Server Error)

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      layerId - The ID of the layer where you want the data ingested.
      byteArray - A byte array of data in SDII MessageList protobuf format to send to the HERE platform for ingestion. The maximum size is 20 MB. Decode the example from base64 before using.
      xHEREChecksum - A base64 encoded SHA-256 hash you can provide for validation against the calculated value on the request body hash. This verifies the integrity of your request and prevents modification by a third party.It will be created by the service if not provided. A SHA-256 hash consists of 256 bits or 64 chars.
      xHERETraceId - A unique message ID, such as a UUID. This can be included in the request if you want to use an ID that you define. If you do not include an ID, one will be generated during ingestion and included in the response. You can use this ID to track your request and identify the message in the catalog.
      xHEREMessageKey - A unique message ID, such as a UUID. This can be included in the request if you want to use an ID that you define. If you do not include an ID, X-HERE-TraceId will be used instead. You can use this ID to specify the partition for the message in the data catalog.
      billingTag - Optional billing tag provided by customer. It will be used in grouping of billing records.
